      "message": "@ed@tanous.net a duplicate link would imply that a `GET` on that collection member could result in either one of the backing D-Bus objects being queried..\n\nIs that so or does bmcweb have a mechanism to always prefer one based on e.g. sorting?\n\nExample:\n\n```\n    {\n      \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/UpdateService/FirmwareInventory/version1\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/UpdateService/FirmwareInventory/version1\"\n    },\n\n```\n\ncorresponding to \n`/xyz/openbmc_project/software/bios/version1` and \n`/xyz/openbmc_project/software/cpld/version1`\n\nLet\u0027s say bmcweb chooses `/xyz/openbmc_project/software/bios/version1` for a query on `version1` member.\n\nThen `/xyz/openbmc_project/software/bios/version1` disappears and bmcweb instead returns `/xyz/openbmc_project/software/cpld/version1` on a GET for `version1` member.\n\nIs that allowed in redfish spec?",
